---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="Cypherlots ‚Äî Journal Foundation"
  description="Personal, encrypted data nodes that enable sharing without surveillance."
>
  <div class="container prose" style="margin-top: var(--space-xl); margin-bottom: var(--space-3xl);">
    <h1>Cypherlots</h1>
    
    <p class="lead">A Cypherlot is a personal, encrypted data node that lets you share exactly what you intend‚Äîwith no platform in the middle.</p>
    
    <div style="background: var(--void-lighter); border-left: 4px solid var(--encrypted-green); padding: var(--space-lg); margin: var(--space-lg) 0;">
      <p><strong>Key insight:</strong> Your data in your basement, not Zuckerberg's data center. That's the whole point.</p>
    </div>
    
    <h2>What Makes Cypherlots Different</h2>
    
    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: var(--space-lg); margin: var(--space-lg) 0;">
      <div style="background: var(--void-lighter); padding: var(--space-lg); border-radius: 8px;">
        <h3>üîí Encrypted by Default</h3>
        <p>Every byte of data is encrypted at rest and in transit. Not optional, not bolted-on‚Äîbuilt in from day one.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div style="background: var(--void-lighter); padding: var(--space-lg); border-radius: 8px;">
        <h3>üé´ Capability-Based Sharing</h3>
        <p>Grant precise, scoped, expiring permissions. Revoke access instantly. No "all or nothing" sharing.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div style="background: var(--void-lighter); padding: var(--space-lg); border-radius: 8px;">
        <h3>üëª Metadata Minimization</h3>
        <p>Blind relays can't read your data or know who you're talking to. Even metadata is protected.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div style="background: var(--void-lighter); padding: var(--space-lg); border-radius: 8px;">
        <h3>üè† Self-Hostable</h3>
        <p>Run on a Raspberry Pi in your basement or a server in your garage. No cloud required.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div style="background: var(--void-lighter); padding: var(--space-lg); border-radius: 8px;">
        <h3>üõ†Ô∏è Not a Platform</h3>
        <p>It's infrastructure. Apps can interoperate without needing a central authority or surveillance.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div style="background: var(--void-lighter); padding: var(--space-lg); border-radius: 8px;">
        <h3>‚ö° No Sacrifice</h3>
        <p>Privacy and convenience aren't mutually exclusive. Good UX with strong security.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <h2>How It Works</h2>
    
    <h3>1. Your Personal Vault</h3>
    <p>A Cypherlot is fundamentally a personal encrypted vault. All your data‚Äîmessages, photos, documents, social posts‚Äîlives encrypted on storage you control.</p>
    
    <h3>2. Capability Tokens</h3>
    <p>Instead of "friend" lists or broad permissions, you grant specific capabilities:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Scope:</strong> What can be accessed (specific files, folders, data types)</li>
      <li><strong>Duration:</strong> How long access lasts (hours, days, permanent)</li>
      <li><strong>Actions:</strong> What can be done (read, write, comment, reshare)</li>
      <li><strong>Revocation:</strong> Instant cancellation of any permission</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h3>3. Blind Relays</h3>
    <p>Optional proxy servers that forward encrypted data without being able to read it or correlate traffic patterns. Even the relay operators can't spy on you.</p>
    
    <h2>Real-World Use Cases</h2>
    
    <div style="margin: var(--space-lg) 0;">
      <h3>Family Photo Sharing</h3>
      <p>Grant your family read access to your "vacation photos" folder for 30 days. They can view and download, but not edit or reshare. Revoke access instantly if needed.</p>
      
      <h3>Collaborative Documents</h3>
      <p>Give your team write access to specific project files. Each person sees only what they need. No corporate platform scanning your documents.</p>
      
      <h3>Social Networking</h3>
      <p>Share posts with different circles‚Äîfamily, work colleagues, hobby groups‚Äîwith granular control over who sees what. No algorithm deciding your reach.</p>
      
      <h3>Secure Messaging</h3>
      <p>Messages that are truly private, with no central server storing metadata about who talks to whom and when.</p>
    </div>
    
    <h2>Why Not Just Use...</h2>
    
    <div style="background: var(--void-lighter); padding: var(--space-lg); border-radius: 8px; margin: var(--space-lg) 0;">
      <h3>Signal, WhatsApp, Telegram?</h3>
      <p>These encrypt message content but not metadata. The platforms still know who you talk to, when, and how often. That metadata is incredibly valuable for profiling and manipulation.</p>
      
      <h3>Mastodon, Diaspora?</h3>
      <p>Federation still centralizes power in server operators. Your data lives on someone else's computer, and privacy is optional. They built platforms, not protocols.</p>
      
      <h3>Solid Pods, IPFS?</h3>
      <p>Close, but focused on data portability rather than privacy. Metadata is still readable, and sharing models are too crude for real-world use.</p>
    </div>
    
    <h2>Current Status</h2>
    
    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr)); gap: var(--space-md); margin: var(--space-lg) 0;">
      <div style="background: rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.1); border: 1px solid var(--urgent-amber); padding: var(--space-md); border-radius: 6px;">
        <h4 style="color: var(--urgent-amber); margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);">üöß In Development</h4>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.9rem;">Core protocol specification and reference implementation</p>
      </div>
      
      <div style="background: rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.1); border: 1px solid var(--encrypted-green); padding: var(--space-md); border-radius: 6px;">
        <h4 style="color: var(--encrypted-green); margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);">‚úÖ Available</h4>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.9rem;">RFC specifications and design documents</p>
      </div>
      
      <div style="background: rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.1); border: 1px solid var(--electric-blue); padding: var(--space-md); border-radius: 6px;">
        <h4 style="color: var(--electric-blue); margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);">üî¨ Research</h4>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.9rem;">Cryptographic protocols and security analysis</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <h2>Get Started</h2>
    
    <div style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.1), rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.1)); padding: var(--space-lg); border-radius: 8px; margin-top: var(--space-xl);">
      <h3>Ready to Run Your Own Cypherlot?</h3>
      
      <div style="margin: var(--space-md) 0;">
        <h4>For Early Adopters:</h4>
        <pre style="background: var(--void); padding: var(--space-md); border-radius: 4px; margin: var(--space-sm) 0;"><code>docker run -d --name cypherlot \
  -p 443:443 \
  -v $HOME/cypherlot:/data \
  ghcr.io/journalfoundation/cypherlot:0.1</code></pre>
      </div>
      
      <div style="display: flex; gap: var(--space-md); justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-top: var(--space-lg);">
        <a href="/specs" style="background: var(--electric-blue); color: var(--void); padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-lg); border-radius: 6px; font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none;">Read the Specs</a>
        <a href="/docs/quickstart" style="border: 2px solid var(--encrypted-green); color: var(--encrypted-green); padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-lg); border-radius: 6px; font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none;">Quick Start Guide</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/journalfoundation" style="border: 2px solid var(--text-muted); color: var(--text-muted); padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-lg); border-radius: 6px; font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none;">View on GitHub</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .lead {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }
  
  h3 {
    color: var(--encrypted-green);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }
  
  h4 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
  }
</style>